WEBVTT

00:01.043 --> 00:03.212
<i>EDWIN: Welcome to Indigo Bay.</i>

00:03.212 --> 00:05.130
<i>ROY: Multiple witnesses
saw Alison</i>

00:05.130 --> 00:07.424
<i>at the bar last night
with two young local men.</i>

00:07.424 --> 00:08.675
And the three of them
left the bar

00:08.675 --> 00:09.760
together around midnight.

00:09.760 --> 00:12.054
Your daughter is
no longer with them.

00:12.054 --> 00:14.473
- <i>PERSON: Gogo!</i>
- [grunts]

00:14.473 --> 00:16.975
Who was that cutie
you were talking to

00:16.975 --> 00:18.227
<i>in the Yale shirt?</i>

00:18.227 --> 00:19.811
EDWIN: I recommend the hike
on Faraway Cay.

00:19.811 --> 00:20.896
CLAIRE: I don't wanna go.

00:20.896 --> 00:22.856
I don't like to go either, Miss.

00:22.856 --> 00:24.107
Ah, the weather.

00:24.107 --> 00:27.236
She always change she mind, Miss.

00:27.236 --> 00:28.904
- Hello?
- Would it be possible

00:28.904 --> 00:30.864
to meet up so I could
get my phone back?

00:30.864 --> 00:32.407
<i>GOGO: Little Sugar.
See you there.</i>

00:34.493 --> 00:38.247
<i>[Luciano Pavarotti's
"La Donna E Mobile"]</i>

00:38.247 --> 00:41.250
[singing along in Italian]

00:41.250 --> 00:48.215
♪ ♪

00:52.469 --> 00:54.346
Shit.

00:54.346 --> 00:57.516
[sirens wailing]

00:57.516 --> 01:01.478
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:01.478 --> 01:03.397
[sighs]

01:03.397 --> 01:10.404
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:24.710 --> 01:27.713
<i>[ominous music]</i>

01:27.713 --> 01:32.217
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:32.217 --> 01:35.095
Mr. Richardson, Mr. Hastings,

01:35.095 --> 01:36.930
out of the car.

01:41.393 --> 01:43.061
You boys,

01:43.061 --> 01:46.356
you're gonna sleep it off
at the station--

01:46.356 --> 01:48.650
again.

01:48.650 --> 01:50.277
Gogo, I should call
your grandma.

01:50.277 --> 01:51.903
You're supposed to be
a father now.

01:51.903 --> 01:54.197
What kind of example
you setting f--

01:54.197 --> 01:58.452
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:58.452 --> 02:02.122
You two
awfully quiet back there.

02:02.122 --> 02:04.249
What y'all been up to?

02:04.249 --> 02:07.544
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:07.544 --> 02:09.296
Javier said there was snow.

02:09.296 --> 02:10.672
We should probably get
the gutters checked

02:10.672 --> 02:12.424
- when we get back.
- Oh, great.

02:12.424 --> 02:13.759
Gutter talk has begun.

02:13.759 --> 02:17.095
Vacation is really over.

02:17.095 --> 02:20.307
Clairey? What is it, sweetie?

02:20.307 --> 02:22.934
Alison didn't come home
last night.

02:22.934 --> 02:25.187
Oh, honey,
I'm sure she's okay.

02:27.189 --> 02:31.109
I'm sorry.

02:31.109 --> 02:32.527
Let's get you packed.

02:32.527 --> 02:39.201
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:40.118 --> 02:41.370
<i>DR. NORTON:
You're not sleeping?</i>

02:41.370 --> 02:43.747
Something on your mind?

02:43.747 --> 02:45.290
No.

02:45.290 --> 02:48.835
No, it--I'm just tired.

02:48.835 --> 02:50.253
Probably the new mattress.

02:52.047 --> 02:54.424
Josh snores sometimes too.

02:54.424 --> 02:57.219
DR. NORTON: No one's perfect.

02:57.219 --> 02:58.845
But he's close.

02:58.845 --> 03:00.514
Josh is the first guy
who's actually fought

03:00.514 --> 03:02.974
to tear down my walls.

03:02.974 --> 03:04.309
[sighs]

03:04.309 --> 03:06.395
He accepts me as flawed
and damaged as I am.

03:08.105 --> 03:09.815
DR. NORTON: I see.

03:09.815 --> 03:13.151
<i>CLAIRE: I'm loving
living together, being a team.</i>

03:13.151 --> 03:14.569
<i>DR. NORTON:
And you're sure moving</i>

03:14.569 --> 03:17.823
<i>to a Caribbean neighborhood
wasn't too much?</i>

03:17.823 --> 03:19.825
<i>CLAIRE:
No. Flatbush is great.</i>

03:21.743 --> 03:22.953
<i>DR. NORTON:
I still wish we could talk</i>

03:22.953 --> 03:24.830
<i>about your history.</i>

03:24.830 --> 03:28.250
<i>Dig in a little.</i>

03:28.250 --> 03:31.086
<i>CLAIRE:
I really don't need to.</i>

03:31.086 --> 03:32.671
<i>I'm better.</i>

03:32.671 --> 03:34.464
<i>You should feel proud
of yourself.</i>

03:34.464 --> 03:36.466
I mean, I'm no longer
the self-destructive mess

03:36.466 --> 03:38.677
you met at the hospital
two years ago.

03:38.677 --> 03:40.095
That's good to hear.

03:40.095 --> 03:44.766
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:44.766 --> 03:46.476
We said
if I was taking care of myself,

03:46.476 --> 03:49.354
we could cut back
to once a month.

03:49.354 --> 03:52.149
I feel like I'm there.
Don't you?

03:53.650 --> 03:56.236
Often,
people choose to quit therapy

03:56.236 --> 03:59.197
exactly when they need it most.

03:59.197 --> 04:01.032
That's really not it.
I'm just...

04:04.327 --> 04:05.328
I'm good.

04:07.038 --> 04:09.749
Well, the choice is yours.

04:09.749 --> 04:13.378
But my door is open
if anything changes.

04:13.378 --> 04:15.672
You've been through a lot, Emily.

04:15.672 --> 04:17.299
Don't forget it.

04:20.427 --> 04:23.221
What are you doing today?

04:23.221 --> 04:24.723
Work.

04:24.723 --> 04:26.475
But first, getting my phone.

04:26.475 --> 04:28.685
I stupidly left it in a cab.

04:28.685 --> 04:35.734
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:02.844 --> 05:05.847
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

05:05.847 --> 05:12.854
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:12.854 --> 05:15.899
[indistinct chatter]

05:18.193 --> 05:19.861
EDWIN: It was Daphne birthday
on top of that.

05:19.861 --> 05:21.404
[indistinct chatter]

05:21.404 --> 05:24.157
Take her to the center
of the dance floor.

05:24.157 --> 05:25.283
GOGO: Edwin, you didn't.

05:25.283 --> 05:26.785
DESMOND: Oh, he did, Goges.

05:26.785 --> 05:28.078
He got up on a table,

05:28.078 --> 05:29.579
and he started doing
the Running Man.

05:29.579 --> 05:31.164
- GOGO: Hmm.
- And the crazy part is,

05:31.164 --> 05:32.707
all the ladies eat his shit up.

05:32.707 --> 05:34.668
EDWIN: Yeah, because--
because I got the moves.

05:34.668 --> 05:36.545
You know--
[vocalizing beat]

05:36.545 --> 05:39.548
[laughter]

05:42.467 --> 05:46.179
And we know who he want
to give those moves to, eh?

05:46.179 --> 05:47.806
EDWIN: Uh-huh.

05:47.806 --> 05:50.392
[Paul laughing]

05:50.392 --> 05:51.852
Right, and when I, uh--

05:51.852 --> 05:53.144
when I asked
for egg whites only,

05:53.144 --> 05:54.437
he looked at me
like I was crazy.

05:54.437 --> 05:56.690
[laughs] You remember
that, uh, green omelet

05:56.690 --> 05:57.983
- from Parrot Caye?
- Yes, I remember

05:57.983 --> 05:59.067
the green omelet
from Parrot Caye.

05:59.067 --> 06:01.278
Hi, I'm Jamie.
Mind if I join you?

06:01.278 --> 06:02.487
Yeah, sure.
GREG: Uh, sure.

06:02.487 --> 06:04.489
Have a seat.

06:04.489 --> 06:05.991
[groans]

06:05.991 --> 06:08.285
I don't know
why we left the nanny at home.

06:08.285 --> 06:09.953
Two days in,
I'm already exhausted.

06:09.953 --> 06:12.038
[chuckles]
But finally,

06:12.038 --> 06:13.373
the kids are at camp

06:13.373 --> 06:15.542
and my husband's playing golf
and I get a break.

06:15.542 --> 06:17.460
Foreign countries
can be so stressful.

06:17.460 --> 06:20.839
Although some people seem
to be acclimating well.

06:20.839 --> 06:22.632
BILL:
Oh, good morning, sunshine.

06:22.632 --> 06:24.759
MIA: I wondered when
we'd see you this morning.

06:24.759 --> 06:26.344
CLAIRE:
Alison went out last night.

06:26.344 --> 06:27.512
- [laughs]
- Claire.

06:27.512 --> 06:28.722
CLAIRE: I was all alone.

06:28.722 --> 06:30.765
I don't like to be alone.

06:30.765 --> 06:32.267
Well, honey,
Alison's in college.

06:32.267 --> 06:33.602
She gets to have a little fun.

06:33.602 --> 06:35.770
Okay, next time, just--
just let us know

06:35.770 --> 06:37.439
so Claire can sleep with us
if she wants.

06:37.439 --> 06:39.316
EDWIN: Good morning, Thomases.

06:39.316 --> 06:40.609
Can I get you
some piña coladas?

06:40.609 --> 06:42.110
- Uh, please, two.
- [Mia laughs]

06:42.110 --> 06:43.778
Yes, and two virgin coladas, please.

06:43.778 --> 06:46.072
- Seriously?
- It's, like, 9:00 a.m., Al.

06:46.072 --> 06:48.033
It's Alison.

06:48.033 --> 06:50.702
MIA: Okay, so spill.
Who were you with last night?

06:50.702 --> 06:52.287
Cutie from Yale?

06:52.287 --> 06:53.663
What?

06:53.663 --> 06:57.250
It hurts me
when you say things like that.

06:58.251 --> 07:00.337
So how'd it go last night?

07:00.337 --> 07:02.672
We had a really great time.

07:02.672 --> 07:05.592
You don't have to fake it
with me, okay?

07:05.592 --> 07:08.595
Look,
if Princeton's too uptight,

07:08.595 --> 07:11.014
what about her?

07:11.014 --> 07:13.808
She seems... attainable.

07:13.808 --> 07:16.811
[indistinct chatter]

07:19.189 --> 07:21.733
You know,
I saw you last night.

07:21.733 --> 07:25.195
With that random dude--
random married dude.

07:25.195 --> 07:27.739
Everyone's random until
you get to know them better.

07:33.620 --> 07:35.872
Two piña coladas.
BILL: Oh.

07:35.872 --> 07:37.957
Thank you.
BILL: Thank you very much.

07:37.957 --> 07:42.128
And two virgin.
You will enjoy them.

07:50.220 --> 07:52.931
[mouthing words]
Thank you.

07:55.058 --> 07:56.768
TYLER:
Alison, I was wondering

07:56.768 --> 07:58.228
if you wanted
to hang out tonight.

07:58.228 --> 08:01.523
Uh, if that's all right
with you, Mr. and Mrs. Thomas.

08:01.523 --> 08:03.566
Well, I mean, we have
early dinner reservations.

08:03.566 --> 08:05.485
- But she's free after--
- I'm actually not sure

08:05.485 --> 08:08.863
what I'm gonna do, but I'll
catch up with you later.

08:08.863 --> 08:11.074
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

08:11.074 --> 08:14.160
<i>CLAIRE:
That guy Tyler is a dork.</i>

08:14.160 --> 08:15.870
He's nice,

08:15.870 --> 08:19.290
and it's fun
to be around kids my own age.

08:19.290 --> 08:21.459
You know what's cool
about vacation?

08:21.459 --> 08:23.044
Nobody knows us.

08:23.044 --> 08:24.587
No one's
ever gonna see us again.

08:24.587 --> 08:28.925
This is our chance
to try on someone new.

08:28.925 --> 08:32.345
I'm Vacation Alison.
Vacation Claire.

08:32.345 --> 08:34.514
It's very nice to meet you.

08:34.514 --> 08:36.433
Why don't you check out
the kids club later?

08:36.433 --> 08:38.143
Vacation Claire's
gonna knock 'em dead.

08:39.853 --> 08:41.312
Hey there.

08:41.312 --> 08:44.482
Thanks for the drink earlier.
I really needed that.

08:44.482 --> 08:47.652
EDWIN: It my job to anticipate
the needs of the guests.

08:47.652 --> 08:51.698
- Duty calls?
- Yeah, nonstop till 3:00.

08:51.698 --> 08:54.034
- What's at 3:00?
- Break.

08:54.034 --> 08:57.495
Usually take it down there
over by the firepit.

09:00.749 --> 09:03.126
DESMOND: D'you remember
that redhead from last year?

09:03.126 --> 09:04.669
Her father almost kill Edwin

09:04.669 --> 09:06.963
when he found they
in the carpark.

09:06.963 --> 09:09.424
Just tell him to be careful.

09:09.424 --> 09:13.303
We can't afford
no more trouble.

09:13.303 --> 09:14.846
<i>ROY:
Multiple witnesses saw Alison</i>

09:14.846 --> 09:17.432
<i>at the bar last night
with two young local men.</i>

09:17.432 --> 09:19.559
And the three of them
left the bar together

09:19.559 --> 09:21.394
around midnight.

09:21.394 --> 09:22.979
I arrested the two men

09:22.979 --> 09:24.439
few hours later
for drunk driving,

09:24.439 --> 09:27.484
but your daughter
was no longer with them.

09:27.484 --> 09:30.070
BILL: Okay, look,
wh-wh-what men?

09:30.070 --> 09:31.196
You don't have to say it.

09:31.196 --> 09:32.947
I know it.
Those two fucking guys.

09:32.947 --> 09:35.116
The fat one and the thin one!

09:35.116 --> 09:37.368
[knocking at door]

09:37.368 --> 09:40.371
<i>[tense music]</i>

09:40.371 --> 09:46.002
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:47.504 --> 09:49.547
I have tea.

09:49.547 --> 09:51.341
From the manager.

09:51.341 --> 09:53.968
You stay the fuck away
from my family, you hear me?

09:53.968 --> 09:57.722
What'd you do to her?
Where's Alison?

09:57.722 --> 10:00.391
Where is she?
What'd you do to her?

10:00.391 --> 10:03.770
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:03.770 --> 10:06.815
[panting]

10:06.815 --> 10:13.822
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:23.122 --> 10:25.667
[bell chimes]

10:27.126 --> 10:29.546
- Emily?
- Yeah.

10:32.382 --> 10:36.219
It's really nice of you
to bring me my phone.

10:36.219 --> 10:38.471
Well, I had no choice.

10:38.471 --> 10:39.597
You could have called dispatch,

10:39.597 --> 10:41.850
accuse me of stealing,
have me fired.

10:41.850 --> 10:44.185
CLAIRE: No--oh, I would--
I would never.

10:46.563 --> 10:48.439
GOGO: Here.

10:48.439 --> 10:51.442
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

10:51.442 --> 10:55.446
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:55.446 --> 10:57.866
This place looks great.

10:57.866 --> 10:59.200
Have you eaten here?

11:00.702 --> 11:02.787
Uh, Little Sugar has
the most authentic food

11:02.787 --> 11:04.664
in the neighborhood.

11:07.375 --> 11:10.044
Well...

11:10.044 --> 11:11.588
- GOGO: No.
- Please, I insist.

11:11.588 --> 11:12.797
No.

11:14.799 --> 11:18.052
Well, um,

11:18.052 --> 11:20.221
thank you, then.

11:20.221 --> 11:27.228
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:27.228 --> 11:30.273
[breathing heavily]

11:36.613 --> 11:38.364
CLAIRE: Guess who's able
to communicate again.

11:38.364 --> 11:39.741
<i>JOSH: Yay!</i>

11:39.741 --> 11:42.619
Wow, that was dope
of the driver to deliver it.

11:42.619 --> 11:44.204
You okay?

11:44.204 --> 11:47.415
<i>You were out of the apartment
before I woke up.</i>

11:47.415 --> 11:49.167
Oh, yeah,
I walked to Dr. Norton.

11:49.167 --> 11:51.044
You know, getting to know
the neighborhood.

11:51.044 --> 11:54.547
Hey, babe,
I just got huge news.

11:54.547 --> 11:56.758
The Hayden case got an appeal.

11:56.758 --> 11:58.343
CLAIRE: No, seriously?

11:58.343 --> 11:59.677
I thought you said
it was impossible.

11:59.677 --> 12:01.012
<i>JOSH: I thought it was,
but now I think</i>

12:01.012 --> 12:02.513
<i>we can actually get him exonerated.</i>

12:02.513 --> 12:03.806
The firm
is celebrating tonight,

12:03.806 --> 12:06.351
and the partners
are all gonna be there.

12:06.351 --> 12:08.061
You'll come, right?

12:08.061 --> 12:10.313
Of course I'll be there.

12:10.313 --> 12:12.065
JOSH:
You're the best. Love you!

12:12.065 --> 12:13.232
CLAIRE: See you later.

12:13.232 --> 12:14.525
<i>JOSH: Okay, bye.</i>

12:14.525 --> 12:16.319
Bye.

12:16.319 --> 12:18.988
Oh, great.
More dry cleaning to pick up.

12:18.988 --> 12:23.034
Fucking so glad I went
to film school for this shit.

12:23.034 --> 12:25.370
Wow, you color-code
your schedules, huh?

12:25.370 --> 12:26.788
- Oh, hey.
- Thanks.

12:26.788 --> 12:28.998
SUNITA: Shrier's been looking
for you, but don't worry.

12:28.998 --> 12:30.959
I told him
you had lady troubles.

12:30.959 --> 12:33.211
So how are you doing?

12:33.211 --> 12:35.213
CLAIRE: I'm kind of shitty,
to be honest.

12:37.882 --> 12:40.260
I can't stop
thinking about him--

12:40.260 --> 12:41.260
or her.

12:42.720 --> 12:44.222
Yeah.

12:44.222 --> 12:46.391
My sister's murder was
headline news for a year.

12:46.391 --> 12:48.351
They made
a fucking TV movie about it.

12:48.351 --> 12:49.769
My parents tried to keep it
from me,

12:49.769 --> 12:52.772
but sometimes it feels like

12:52.772 --> 12:54.941
the whole world knows
more about what happened to her

12:54.941 --> 12:56.859
than I do.

12:56.859 --> 12:58.861
Trust me,
your parents are right.

12:58.861 --> 13:00.488
There's no good answers
out there.

13:00.488 --> 13:03.950
It's just awful internet shit.

13:03.950 --> 13:06.786
Promise me you won't look.

13:06.786 --> 13:08.413
I'm not gonna look.

13:08.413 --> 13:09.706
It's too deep a rabbit hole,

13:09.706 --> 13:12.000
and I know
it's not good for me.

13:12.000 --> 13:13.876
Did you tell Dr. Norton?

13:16.170 --> 13:18.423
Did you tell Josh?

13:18.423 --> 13:21.843
Em, I think knowing
his girlfriend got into a cab

13:21.843 --> 13:24.637
with the man who killed
her sister is important.

13:26.556 --> 13:29.475
He's gonna love you
no matter what, you know?

13:29.475 --> 13:32.061
All right, enough. Shoo.

13:32.061 --> 13:33.938
SUNITA: All right.

13:33.938 --> 13:36.024
I have bear drama to edit.

13:37.650 --> 13:39.277
SUNITA: Kay.

13:44.824 --> 13:47.827
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

13:47.827 --> 13:54.834
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:13.227 --> 14:16.272
<i>[water rushing]</i>

14:25.281 --> 14:26.908
EDWIN: You see
the boss man got new chairs

14:26.908 --> 14:28.659
for the whities?

14:28.659 --> 14:31.662
To cushion they tender asses.
[laughs]

14:31.662 --> 14:34.040
Anyway, got news.

14:34.040 --> 14:35.792
Oh, no.

14:35.792 --> 14:37.585
No, when you be showing me
all them teeth,

14:37.585 --> 14:39.128
always mean trouble.

14:39.128 --> 14:41.547
No, no, not trouble, big man.

14:41.547 --> 14:43.382
Opportunity.

14:43.382 --> 14:45.051
Desmond cousin hook we up

14:45.051 --> 14:47.136
with a meeting
with One-Eye Mike.

14:47.136 --> 14:49.263
No.
EDWIN: What you mean "no"?

14:49.263 --> 14:51.057
You say yourself
you need money for Sara.

14:51.057 --> 14:52.600
That your thing.

14:52.600 --> 14:54.435
Cocaine way more serious
than we usual shit.

14:54.435 --> 14:55.645
I won't be risking it.

14:55.645 --> 14:57.480
This a good job.
We make good tips.

14:57.480 --> 14:59.315
I make good tips.

14:59.315 --> 15:00.858
You still strugglin',

15:00.858 --> 15:02.652
which be why
I decide to include you.

15:02.652 --> 15:05.321
No, Edwin.
No more foolin' around.

15:05.321 --> 15:07.156
- EDWIN: [chuckles]
- No more crime.

15:07.156 --> 15:08.741
I got a steady job.

15:08.741 --> 15:09.992
I will provide for my family.

15:09.992 --> 15:11.953
I will make
Sara and Clive Jr. proud.

15:11.953 --> 15:16.707
Think how proud they be
when you buy a bike for Clive,

15:16.707 --> 15:19.168
when you buy
a dishwasher for Sara.

15:22.588 --> 15:25.758
One-Eye Mike
a real drug dealer.

15:25.758 --> 15:28.636
One-Eye Mike be
a business man, same as we.

15:28.636 --> 15:30.304
- GOGO: You never met him.
- Neither have you.

15:32.515 --> 15:34.308
I won't go.

15:34.308 --> 15:39.188
Ah, how such a big man can be
such a little chicken...

15:39.188 --> 15:41.440
[chuckles]
